WEBVTT

00:00:00.620 --> 00:00:05.620
Let's look at the entirety of Melachi chapter 3 and verse 16.

00:00:05.620 --> 00:00:09.619
In fact, what we'll do is read just the first part of it.

00:00:09.619 --> 00:00:12.619
Melachi 3, 16.

00:00:12.619 --> 00:00:18.620
At that time, those who feared Jehovah spoke with one another,

00:00:18.620 --> 00:00:21.620
each one with his companion,

00:00:21.620 --> 00:00:27.620
and Jehovah kept paying attention and listening.

00:00:27.620 --> 00:00:32.619
Now, did you notice that Jehovah is paying attention and listening to how we speak

00:00:32.619 --> 00:00:34.619
to one another?

00:00:34.619 --> 00:00:39.619
Why would Jehovah record the names of those who do just that,

00:00:39.619 --> 00:00:42.619
speaking to one another in the way that pleases him?

00:00:42.619 --> 00:00:48.619
Why would he list them in the book of life?

00:00:48.619 --> 00:00:53.619
Well, it's because our speech reflects what's in our hearts.

00:00:53.619 --> 00:01:01.619
Jesus said, as we all know, a good man brings forth a good treasure out of his heart.

00:01:01.619 --> 00:01:07.620
But a wicked man brings forth what is wicked out of his wicked treasure

00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:11.620
for out of the heart's abundance, the mouth speaks.

00:01:11.620 --> 00:01:14.620
Now, that's pretty deep.

00:01:14.620 --> 00:01:20.620
What we say reflects what we really are inside.

00:01:20.620 --> 00:01:28.620
When we think about others, it's much easier to say things in a negative way.

00:01:28.620 --> 00:01:34.620
The saying is that it's easier to tear down a building than it is to build one new.

00:01:34.620 --> 00:01:37.620
And all of us have faults.

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:43.620
King Solomon said, there's no righteous man in the earth that keeps doing good

00:01:43.620 --> 00:01:46.620
and does not sin.

00:01:46.620 --> 00:01:54.620
Now, it takes a lot for us to have the gift of finding good.

00:01:54.620 --> 00:02:00.620
It does not take so much to identify someone's shortcomings.

00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:07.620
And we have to be careful how we talk to and about each other.

00:02:07.620 --> 00:02:14.620
What helps is if we focus on people the way Jehovah sees them.

00:02:14.620 --> 00:02:17.620
It calls them precious.

00:02:17.620 --> 00:02:23.620
And we all remember so well the words of Jesus at John, chapter 6, verse 44,

00:02:23.620 --> 00:02:29.620
that no one comes to me unless the father who sent me draws him.

00:02:29.620 --> 00:02:33.620
So every one of Jehovah's dedicated people have been drawn by him,

00:02:33.620 --> 00:02:38.620
in spite of their quirks and challenging personalities.

00:02:38.620 --> 00:02:46.620
Yet that one pronoun there to our quirks and personalities.

00:02:46.620 --> 00:02:51.620
But Jehovah sees positive things in every one of us,

00:02:51.620 --> 00:02:56.620
even though we feel that some have challenging personalities.

00:02:56.620 --> 00:03:03.620
But by putting forth every effort to identify each other's good qualities,

00:03:03.620 --> 00:03:08.620
the reason to speak positively to them and about them.

00:03:08.620 --> 00:03:12.620
It's easy to talk about someone in a negative way.

00:03:12.620 --> 00:03:18.620
But imagine if we have to say to them what we say to others about them,

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:23.620
then it should conjure up in us every effort to be positive.

00:03:23.620 --> 00:03:28.620
Now, it doesn't mean that we shouldn't offer counsel if we see the need to offer.

00:03:28.620 --> 00:03:31.620
It's not a matter of offering counsel or not.

00:03:31.620 --> 00:03:35.620
It's a matter of how it's delivered.

00:03:35.620 --> 00:03:41.620
Let's notice what the Bible says in James chapter 1 and verse 26.

00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:43.620
We've all read it many times.

00:03:43.620 --> 00:03:46.620
It makes a powerful point.

00:03:46.620 --> 00:03:53.620
There, James says, if any man thinks he's a worshiper of God.

00:03:53.620 --> 00:03:56.620
So he's not talking to people on the outside.

00:03:56.620 --> 00:04:00.620
He's talking to those within the congregation.

00:04:00.620 --> 00:04:02.620
We're a worshiper of God.

00:04:02.620 --> 00:04:07.620
And we do not keep a tight reign on our tongue.

00:04:07.620 --> 00:04:09.620
What does he say?

00:04:09.620 --> 00:04:14.620
He is deceiving his own heart and his worship is futile.

00:04:14.620 --> 00:04:20.620
So how we use our tongue is a serious matter before Jehovah.

00:04:20.620 --> 00:04:26.620
Jehovah would not be pleased with us if we talk one way,

00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:30.620
we find gracious in meetings and in the ministry,

00:04:30.620 --> 00:04:34.620
but spoke harshly at other times.

00:04:34.620 --> 00:04:40.620
Now, go back to Melachi, if you would, in chapter 3 again, and verse 17.

00:04:40.620 --> 00:04:49.899
And notice the declarations Jehovah makes about such ones who watch their speech.

00:04:49.899 --> 00:04:55.899
And they will be mine, says Jehovah of armies,

00:04:55.899 --> 00:04:59.899
in the day when I produce a special property.

00:04:59.899 --> 00:05:01.899
Now, that's really something.

00:05:01.899 --> 00:05:04.899
Parents have a special bond with their children.

00:05:04.899 --> 00:05:09.899
A single man was visiting his friend who was married and had two children.

00:05:09.899 --> 00:05:12.899
And he observed the little girl.

00:05:12.899 --> 00:05:17.899
She was about five years old, but she was so in need of attention,

00:05:17.899 --> 00:05:19.899
almost distracting her father.

00:05:19.899 --> 00:05:22.899
